      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A software glitch or a temporary loss of power is a more plausible explanation. It's possible that a brief power outage or a Wi-Fi connection issue caused the thermostat to malfunction. Many Nest thermostats have a \"get out of jail free\" system that resets itself after a short period of inactivity, but this should be manually triggered or scheduled. You might want to try restarting the app, device, or router to see if that resolves the issue.",
