      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Since restarting the router and thermostat didn't resolve the issue, it's less likely to be a software glitch. To check for hardware issues, you can try pressing the \"force temperature change\" button on the thermostat for a few hours to see if it manually swings the temperature. Alternatively, you can contact Nest customer support to have them run the Attest function on your device, which helps identify potential hardware or software issues.",
